    "facts": ["170k CS arXiv papers as citation network; year split (≤2017 / 2018 / ≥2019); MAG-derived."],
    "hypotheses": [
      "The 2017-2018 boundary is a natural break (driven by an arXiv categorization shift and volume jump), not merely a convenient cut point.",
      "Method degradation does not track the time gap monotonically (2019 vs 2020 vs 2021) but is threshold-like, jumping at the categorization break."
    ],
    "intuitions": [
      "Extensions of ogbn-arxiv with later test years likely already exist in the literature.",
      "ogbl-citation2 (similar temporal structure on full arXiv) probably provides a useful cross-comparison."
    ],
    "unknowns": [
      "The field-of-study taxonomy itself evolved post-2017 (ML categories proliferated); whether the resulting shift is concept shift (taxonomy change) or covariate shift (volume) cannot be determined from the data.",
